<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 91.28 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 28 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Monday gained 91.28 points to
3,054.73 as against last weekend's close of 2,963.45.
</P>
<P>
The national index also gained 42.87 points to 1,356.92 as
against the previous close of 1,314.05.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar index were quoted higher at 313.12
and 122.61 points compared with the last close of 303.80 and
118.90 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities on the BSE market Monday spurted sharply due to bull
support by foreign funds and domestic institutions.
</P>
<P>
The entry of the foreign institutional investors into the
market sent ripples among the investors and leading institutions
and speculators created fresh positions on the first day of the
current account to book profits later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
