<HEADLINE> China Holds Central Conference on Rural Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 28 (Xinhua) -- The Central Conference on
Rural Work, which will decide the major tasks and goal for the
development of China's rural economy in the next year, opened here
today.
</P>
<P>
In a speech delivered at the opening ceremony of the
conference, Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao said that the fundamental task
for China's rural work in the next year and for the coming period
is to seriously implement the guidelines of the Third Plenum of
the 15th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
The Plenum, which was held in mid-October, passed a "Decision
on Certain Major Issues Concerning Agriculture and Work in the
Rural Areas".
</P>
<P>
"This Decision provides us with the guiding principles for
building socialist new rural areas in China," said Wen, who is
also a member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
He noted that in the past year China has scored remarkable
progress in the field of agriculture, achieving good harvests
despite the negative impact of a series of major natural
disasters. The country's grain production is almost the same as
last year's level, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said, township enterprises in the rural areas
continued to develop despite the influence of global economic
problems, while new progress has been made in promoting democracy
and building the legal system throughout the vast rural areas.
</P>
<P>
During the conference, he noted, the participants need to make
a careful analysis of the current situation in the Chinese
countryside, find solutions to major problems that now exist, and
make good arrangement for the rural work of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Heads of relevant departments of the State Council, China's
cabinet, and of the CPC Central Committee, as well as leaders in
charge of agricultural development and rural work in all
provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities across the nation
attended the conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
