<HEADLINE> Romania: Jobless to Benefit from More </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 28 (Xinhua) -- The National Agency for the
Employment and Vocational Training (ANOFP) will be set in place in
1999, the Rompres news agency reported on Monday citing sources at
the Ministry of Labor and Social Security.
</P>
<P>
ANOFP will grant more advantages to the unemployed and
opportunities to find a job, said the sources. The employment
services will address the people in search for a job and will
ensure the unemployed consultancy and information over how to
develop a business on their own.
</P>
<P>
The agency will also teach the unemployed how to receive a
credit for setting in place a small- or medium-sized company and
new jobs.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also forecasts active measures to pursue the
unemployed stimulation in finding a job.
</P>
<P>
As a new passive measure, the ministry said, it is mandatory
that the unemployment benefit be given in various forms according
to each person's length in service. Therefore, the unemployed with
up to five years length in service will receive 50 percent of the
benefit to the gross average wage gained in the last three months
of work minus the wage tax. The people who have worked for five to
fifteen years will receive an unemployment benefit by 55 percent
of the gross average wage received in the last three months. The
unemployed with more than fifteen years length in service will be
granted 60 percent of the gross average wage on the grounds of the
same calcula.
</P>
<P>
Romania's Work Force and Unemployment Offices scored on
December 21 as many as 962,183 unemployed, with a national
unemployment rate of 9.7 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
