<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People Killed in Traffic Accidents Increase in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 28 (Xinhua) -- The number of people killed in
traffic accidents in October stood at 784, which represents a 2.5
percent increase over the same month 1997, said the official
Securite Routiere on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a total of 15,397 people were injured in traffic
accidents in October, or a 4.7 percent drop as compared with the
same month last year.
</P>
<P>
A total of 8,312 people were killed on the road in 12 months up
till the end of October, a 3.2 percent increase over the same
period one year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The number of people killed in traffic accidents in 1998 is
expected to be about the same as those in 1992 and 1994.  
</P>
</TEXT>
