<HEADLINE> French Police Re-open Caribbean Port by Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 28 (Xinhua) -- French police Monday reopened by
force the port of Fort-de-France in the Caribbean overseas
department of Martinique, which has been blocked by striking
agricultural workers since the end of November.
</P>
<P>
The prefect of region of Martinique Dominique Bellion said that
thousands of containers, some of which contain products of primary
necessity, have been remaining in the port because of the
blockade.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural workers are protesting the EU policy on the
trade of bananas.
</P>
<P>
A poll conducted after the residents of Martinique said that 85
percent of the local people approved a police action against the
strikers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
