<HEADLINE> Credits to be Granted for Dwellings in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Romanian youth and young
families will be able to buy easier a house in 1999, the national
Rompres news agency reported on Monday citing sources at the
Ministry of Public Works and Land Development.
</P>
<P>
According to the ministry, the National Agency for Houses will
analyze annually the bids for crediting the houses' construction
on the grounds of expert studies carried out in cooperation with
the local public administration.
</P>
<P>
The facilities to get credits include a smaller interest rate;
the access to lands for houses' building in special conditions;
tax exemptions for land and dwelling on the entire period of
paying credit back; tax exemption on the profit from rents in case
the dwellings are leased over the credit's paying back period.
</P>
<P>
There is a great short of public housing in Romania, and as
many as one million families are waiting for an apartment.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the government allotted several hundred
million U.S. dollars from the state budget for the completion of
works on 36,147 flats.
</P>
<P>
The government on August passed a mortgage credit bill in a bid
to speed up the houses' construction.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
