<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Closes Mining Areas in Underfavored Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, December 28 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian Government
decided recently to include three mining areas of the country,
totalling 250,000 hectares, among the underfavored areas for the
next ten years.
</P>
<P>
Under the Government's decision, Brad, the Jiu Valley and Balan
areas were added to the beneficiaries of the provisions in the
recently passed Underfavored Areas Law and Regional Development
Law. Thus, people of these areas will benefit from a 10-year, 50
percent deduction in local transport taxes, income taxes, and tax
exemption from farm income.
</P>
<P>
Profit of the economic companies operating in the areas will
also be tax-exempt, and the companies will be prioritarily granted
Government-guaranteed credits to boost exports of manufactured
products and industrial services.
</P>
<P>
The companies will also be reimbursed for customs duties paid
on imports of technology, equipment, know-how, spare parts and raw
material.
</P>
<P>
According to the Underfavored Areas Law, a region is declared
Underfavored area when the local unemployment rate exceeds 25
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
