<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Law for Healthy Development of Securities Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- China's first Securities Law,
which was promulgated here today, is a great achievement of the
nation's reforms and opening up to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
The law, adopted by the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress, the country's top legislative body, will play
an important role in forming a sound socialist market economy,
establishing a socialist legislative system, and protecting the
healthy development of China's securities market.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the law will promote the pooling of funds,
protect the legitimate rights and interests of investors, and
prevent and resolve financial risks.
</P>
<P>
In creating the law, legislators drew lessons from the Asian
financial crisis and China's experiences during the development of
its financial sector.
</P>
<P>
With three fundamental principles governing the issuance of
stocks -- openness, equity and fairness -- the new law will help
standardize, supervise and regulate the immature securities market
in China. The law will also strictly prohibit fraud, insider
trading and market manipulation.
</P>
<P>
The new Securities Law will become effective on July 1, 1999,
and the next thing for the Chinese people to do is to study and
understand it, and use it as a weapon to protect their legitimate
rights.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
