<HEADLINE> Thai Veeraphol Wins WBC Title with Knockout </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 29 (Xinhuha) -- Veeraphol Nakonluang-Promotion
of Thailand knocked out defending champion Joichiro Tatsuyoshi of
Japan in the sixth round to capture the World Boxing Council
(WBC) bantamweight title Tuesday night in Osaka of Japan.
</P>
<P>
The knockout came at two minutes and 52 seconds into the sixth
round when Veeraphol landed a right on Tatsuyoshi's jaw following
a series of smashing blows.
</P>
<P>
When Tatsuyoshi got up, Veeraphol ended the battle with a
series of smashing left and right straight blows. Tatsuyoshi fell
backward to the floor and lay for about a minute before trainers
and doctors revived him.
</P>
<P>
Up until the fifth round, Tatsuyoshi was leading 48-47 on
American judge Gale Van Hoy's scorecard.
</P>
<P>
Veeraphol was ahead 49-46 on American judge Marty Sammon's
card and 48-47 on Mexican Ray Solis' card.
</P>
<P>
Tatsuyoshi was making his third defense of the title he won
from Thailand's Sirimongkol Nakornthorn-Parkview in November 1997.
</P>
<P>
It was Veeraphol's 21st victory, including 15 knockouts and one
defeat.
</P>
<P>
Tatsuyoshi, whose career has been threatened by a retina
injury, now has 17 victories, including 12 knockouts, against
five defeats and one draw. 
</P>
</TEXT>
