<HEADLINE> Demonstration in Somali Capital to Show Power of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mogadishu, December 29 (Xinhua)-- A large muscle-flexing
demonstration sponsored by the faction leaders of the Somali
capital was held Tuesday to show the power of the newly announced
administration of Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
The demonstration coincided with the festive arrangement which
marks the conclusion of training for the first 2,100 police force
encamped for the restoration of law and order in the chaotic
capital Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
According to Colonel Abdi Hassan Awale Qeybdid, police
commander for Mugadishu, the police forces have been given all
necessary professional tactics plus what he called a training for
the special circumstances of the capital.
</P>
<P>
"The activities of the police will start from securing the
stability of Mogadishu and work toward the reopening of the air
and seaports as their first priorities," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also called on the people of Mogadishu to collaborate and
help the policemen for their own interests.
</P>
<P>
"Today is the beginning of a new era for Mogadishu's people,"
said faction leader Ali Mahdi Mohamed, adding the policemen of
the capital are now capable of making a peaceful environment for
the people of the capital.
</P>
<P>
Ali Mahdi said the aim of the administration include the
reconciliation among the people in Mogadishu who after eight
years are still suffering from the closure of the air and
seaports.
</P>
<P>
"We are working for the re-establishment of the law and order
so that our people can live in peace. We welcome our opposition
elements if they have any better ideas. It is now time to forgive
each other and forget about the past," said Ali Mahdi.
</P>
<P>
The demonstration is the first such parade since the collapse
of the late regime in 1991. The former regime used to conduct
such activity once every year on 21 October which was the day
when Major General Mohamed Siad Barre came into power in a
bloodless coup. 
</P>
