<HEADLINE> Sweden's Birth Rate Hits New Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's birth rate hit a
new low this year with each woman of childbearing age giving
birth to an average 1.5 children, according to official figures
issued Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
 This marked the second consecutive year in which the birth
rate was lower than the death rate. In 1998, Sweden's birth rate
stood at 1.01 percent, or 90,000 babies, but the death rate was
1.05 percent, or 93,000 deaths.
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, a total of 50,000 foreign immigrants arrived in
the Scandinavian country and around 39,000 Swedish nationals
emigrated.
</P>
<P>
 Sweden's population reached 8.85 million with an increase of
8,000 over last year. 
</P>
