<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Three people on board a Myanmar
patrol boat were wounded by fire shot from one of the 15 foreign
trawler vessels poaching in Myanmar territorial waters on December
19, state-run Radio Myanmar reported Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
When the Myanmar patrol boat found the trawler vessels poaching
near Zadetgyi Island in the country's southern Tanintharyi
division at North Latitude 9'50.5" and East Longitude 98'7.5", it
ordered them to stop for investigation.
</P>
<P>
However, one of the vessels then started firing, wounding the
three and fled into Thai territorial waters, the report said.
</P>
