<HEADLINE> Dhaka Takes up Judicial Capacity Building Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has
taken up a judicial and legal capacity building project involving
60 million U.S. dollars for increasing efficiency of the judicial
and legal system, the official BSS news agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank (WB) will provide 45 million dollars for the
project, while the government will provide the rest of the amount,
and the Ministry of Law and Justice will implement the project.
</P>
<P>
The main objective of the project is to increase efficiency of
the judicial and legal system through improvement of the legal
framework, streamlining the system of courts and strengthening the
judicial capacity and providing improved access to justice.
</P>
<P>
The government is negotiating with the WB for reaching an
agreement by next April so that the project could be launched in
the middle of 1999, the report said.
</P>
<P>
A series of meetings have been held between Bangladesh and the
WB on the loan negotiation for the project, and the WB in its
board meeting next March may give approval of the credit.
</P>
<P>
Now, the government is completing all procedural requirements
including approval of technical assistance project profile,
project concept paper and project profile before signing the
agreement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
