lies in the fact that he never attached importance to study and
self improvement, had no political awareness, coveted the
comforts and luxuries of life, and cherished no ideal or lofty
pursuit.
</P>
<P>
"All Party and government officials must draw a bitter lesson
from the case of Meng, and treasure the power granted them by the
