<HEADLINE> China's 1998 Treasury Bond Issues Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- China completed this year's
issuance of treasury bonds on December 28, the Ministry of Finance
announced today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 220 billion yuan in certificate bonds were sold in
1998, and 51.3 million yuan in treasury bonds issued to
securities exchanges for business banks and insurance companies.
</P>
<P>
In addition, China issued 9.5 billion yuan in treasury bonds to
social security and business insurance agencies this year, and
sold one billion U.S. dollars in global treasury bonds worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The last batch of this year's treasury bonds, which were issued
last week to securities exchanges for 19 business banks and
insurance companies, are seven-year account bonds valued at nine
billion yuan.  
</P>
