<HEADLINE> China Reports Success in Crackdown on Vehicle Theft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- China said today that public
security departments across the country have dealt with 34,000
cases of motor vehicle theft during the national crackdown
campaign over last two months.
</P>
<P>
Over 25,000 people involved in the thefts were arrested,
according to a press official of the Ministry of Public Security.
</P>
<P>
Police also solved over 3,500 cases of vehicle robbery and
seized 3,600 smuggled and stolen cars, in addition to about 23,000
motorcycles.
</P>
<P>
The official said support from the general public has been
decisive for the success of the campaign. The ministry has
received more than 1,500 phone calls through a hot line for
reporting vehicle theft which has provided help in over 300 cases.
</P>
<P>
Police departments in seven provinces including Guangdong,
Liaoning, and Anhui have returned some 1,000 vehicles to their
legitimate owners.  
</P>
</TEXT>
