<HEADLINE> Shanghai-Hangzhou Highway Opens to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The entire Huhang Highway
from Shanghai to Hangzhou, capital of east China's Zhejiang
Province, was opened to traffic today, shortening the trip between
these two cities to a one and a half hour drive.
</P>
<P>
The 151-kilometer-long highway is designed for speeds up to
120 kilometers per hour, and has two lanes in each direction. The
road was funded with loans from the World Bank.
</P>
<P>
Economists say the highway will be of great importance for
helping promote economic development of the Yangtze River
Delta. It will be integrated with the Hangzhou-Ningbo Highway and
become a "golden channel" for goods transported between Shanghai
and most of Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The highway will be operated by the Zhejiang Huhangyong Highway
Co., Ltd., which has listed H shares in Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
