<HEADLINE> China to Decrease Planting Area of Outdated Grain Varieties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- China plans to gradually
decrease the planting area of outdated grain varieties, such as
spring wheat in northeast China and early paddy rice in the
southern part of the country, said Minister of Agriculture Chen
Yaobang today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the on-going working conference on agriculture, Chen
said that to stabilize grain output, China will pay more
attention to improving grain breeds, and that high-quality rice,
wheat specially for processing, and high-protein corn will be
developed.
</P>
<P>
Chen noted that the time is now favorable for readjusting the
rural economic structure because there is a sufficient supply of
grain.
</P>
<P>
China also plans to stabilize cotton production in the
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region and decrease the planting area
of cotton in Hebei, Shandong and Henan provinces and in the
Yangtze River Valley.  
</P>
</TEXT>
