<HEADLINE> China Issues Circular on Euro-Related Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The China State Administration
of Foreign Exchange (SAFE) today issued a circular regulating the
Euro-related activities of domestic institutions.
</P>
<P>
The circular contains regulations on such issues as the
conversion of accounts from the original currencies of European
countries into Euro accounts, the opening of Euro accounts,
foreign debt quota, foreign exchange statistics reports, and the
Euro exchange rate.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the SAFE said these regulations are
designed to provide convenience for domestic institutions and
enterprises doing business in the Euro.
</P>
<P>
Domestic institutions are required to register with the SAFE
before they convert or open their accounts, reflecting the
principle of no restrictions and no prohibitions on the use of the
Euro. It will be beneficial for the SAFE to have an overall
knowledge of the status of Euro accounts, according to the
spokesman. 
</P>
