<HEADLINE> Bank Robber Sentenced to Death in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Guo Hui, a 20-year-old bank
robber who killed a female bank assistant in November 1998, was
sentenced to death by the First Intermediate People's Court of
Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Guo, a former employee of the Postal Administration Bureau of
Daxing County in the southern suburbs of Beijing, was dismissed by
his employer because of incompetency in October 1998.
</P>
<P>
After being dismissed, Guo planned to rob the postal savings
bank on Longhe Road in Daxing County as revenge.
</P>
<P>
He broke into the bank at noon on November 14, 1998 and killed
Zhang Li, the only bank assistant on duty at the time.
</P>
<P>
Guo came away from the robbery with only about 5,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Guo's girlfriend, 18-year-old Ruan Fang, was also sentenced to
three years in jail because of giving false testimony and covering
up for her boyfriend.  
</P>
</TEXT>
