</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981229.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao to Ban Tobacco Advertisements From New Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Macao will ban tobacco
advertisements beginning January 1 next year, sources from the
Macao Municipal Council said.
</P>
<P>
The ban will be implemented in accordance with a government
decree on smoking prevention and restriction. According to the
decree issued in 1997, tobacco publicity includes tobacco
advertisements and tobacco business promotion.
</P>
<P>
The former is aimed at attracting people to buy and consume
certain tobacco products while the latter displays the trademark,
symbol, price, origin and relevant materials of tobacco products.
</P>
<P>
The decree stipulates that all tobacco advertisements are to be
banned while tobacco business promotion will be restricted within
a range of five meters from the site where tobacco products are
sold, and promotion boards cannot exceed three meters in length or
width. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
