<HEADLINE> Anarchist Group Claims Responsibility for Explosions in Athens. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The "Revolutionary Nuclei", an
anarchist group in Greece, has claimed responsibility for two
powerful bombs explosions that shattered two foreign-owned banks
in the port city of Piraeus shortly after midnight Monday, police
said Tuesday.
</P>
