<HEADLINE> S. Leonean Rebel Leader Feared Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Sierra Leonean rebel leader Saj
Musa has been feared dead from injuries sustained in a gun battle
with the west African peacekeeping force ECOMOG on Christmas eve.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued Monday in Nigeria's capital Abuja,
ECOMOG Press Secretary Malam Buhari Ali said that Musa died in "a
fierce battle" between ECOMOG troops and the rebel force under
his command in a desperate attempt to attack the Benguma Military
Training Center near Freetown, capital of Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that ECOMOG had averted an attempt by
rebels to infiltrate Freetown with weapons after intercepting a
boat that was discharging arms and ammunition near the Cape
Sierra Hotel in Freetown, Nigerian news paper Daily Times
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The arms have been seized by the ECOMOG troops while the
captain of the boat is under interrogation, it added.
</P>
<P>
Secretary-General of the Economic Community of West African
States (ECOWAS), Lansana Kouyata, said Monday at an emergency
meeting over the crisis in Abidjan, capital of Cote d'Ivoire that
member states "must reinforce ECOMOG troops."
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that apart from Ghana, Nigeria and Guinea, "we
are still waiting for soldiers from the rest of the region."
</P>
<P>
After a spate of recent attacks by rebels of the Revolutionary
United Front (RUF) near Freetown, ECOMOG is said to have deployed
5,000 soldiers in the area, which are reportedly backed by
another 5,000 traditional fighters from the Kamajor militia.
</P>
<P>
Togo's Foreign Minister Joseph Kocou Koffigoh told the
meeting that the United Nations and the Netherlands have "given
the green light" to finance contingents of 400 Malian soldiers
and another 100 from Gambia.
</P>
<P>
Other countries including Cote d'Ivoire, Niger and Benin have
pledged to send troops to Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG troops and RUF rebels engaged in heavy battles at the
weekend in the northern town of Makeni, where both sides claimed
to be in control.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, rebels threatened to attack Freetown within two
to three days and claimed they had taken two neighboring towns,
Waterloo and Benguema, some 30 kilometers away. 
</P>
</TEXT>
