<HEADLINE> Russian Defense Minister Urges Preserving Nuclear Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Russia should preserve its
nuclear striking potential and meanwhile continue the military
reform, Russian Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This will ensure that no one would think about dealing with
Russia by means of force as they deal with Iraq, said the
minister in an interview with the Segodnya newspaper.
</P>
<P>
He was referring to the United States and Britain, which
bombed Iraq earlier this month without the approval of the United
Nations.
</P>
<P>
Russia has been spending too much to feed the army but too
little to develop military technology and equipment, he said.
</P>
<P>
The modern equipment in an army with combativeness should
account for at least 70 percent of its arsenal, said Sergeyev.
</P>
