<HEADLINE> Share Prices Move Higher in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices moved higher in
Tokyo Tuesday, led by high tech-related blue chips, following
Monday's rise on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange rose 137.84 points, or 1.01
percent, from Monday's close to end at 13,846.90.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering
all First Section issues, added 8.94 points or 0.33 percent to
1,088.83.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section remained thin ahead of the
year-end and New Year holidays in Japan, coming to 219.29 million
shares, up slightly from Monday's 191.79 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Traders said investors generally took a wait-and-see attitude
as they tried to confirm if the bond market has regained
stability following the sharp falls in government bond prices
last week.
</P>
<P>
Sakura Bank was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
High tech-related blue chips gained as the favorable
performances of Internet-related issues in New York Monday had a
positive impact on Japanese counterparts, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers outpaces
losers 635 to 435, with 212 issues ending unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
