<HEADLINE> E.U. Provides Mozambique With $35M in Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission
mission in Maputo said in a press release that the
European Union recently provided an aid of some 35 million U.S.
Dollars to Mozambique in support for the country's budget.
</P>
<P>
The press release carried in Tuesday's
Noticias newspaper that the fund is part of the aid program
agreed in August between the E.U. and the Mozambican government.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the E.U. will provide another 950
billion Metical (some 67.8 million European Currency Unit) for
the structural adjustment program of the southern African
country.
</P>
<P>
The money will go to health, education and road projects due
to be implemented in two years.
</P>
<P>
The press release noted that the E.U. aid program is designed to
support the Mozambican government's economic and structural
reforms, particularly the reform of the public administrative
organs, to ensure that all people can enjoy the basic services.
</P>
<P>
Expectedly, the E.U. will provide 88.5 billion Metical in aid
to Mozambique in 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
