<HEADLINE> Kenya Lifts Ban on Uganda Gin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Kenya has lifted the ban on
the importation of Uganda Waragi to the country as a result of
bilateral discussions on the matter.
</P>
<P>
A press release from Uganda Export Promotion Board said
Tuesday that this achievement is attributed to the talks between
Kenya and Uganda during the Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi's
visit to Kampala on May 19-21, 1998 as well as the follow-up
meetings.
</P>
<P>
"The lifting of the ban by the Kenya government is good news
for the Ugandan exporters who may now revive their old contacts
and establish new ones," said the press release.
</P>
<P>
Every time Uganda has exhibited its Waragi at regional or
international trade shows, it has proved extremely popular among
customers, it added.
</P>
<P>
The years-long ban was reportedly imposed to protect local
wine market by the Kenyan government.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the Uganda Manufacturers' Association, James
Mulwana has demanded for the lifting of the ban several times. He
asked Kenyan President Moi to lift the ban and promote bilateral
trade when the latter came to open an international trade fair
here in early October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
