BEIJING -- China's top legislative body Tuesday approved the
Explanations on Implementation of the Law on Nationality in the
Macao Special Administrative Region (MSAR).
</P>
<P>
China will deal with questions concerning the nationality of
Macao residents in a flexible manner which fully complies with the
 basic principles of the Law on Nationality and considers both
the reality and history of the region.
</P>
<P>
The Explanations read:
</P>
<P>
-- All Macao residents of Chinese descent who were born on
Chinese territory, including Macao, and those fulfilling the req
uirements of the Law on Nationality are Chinese citizens,
regardless of whether they do or do not hold Portuguese travel
certificates or identity cards.(China-Macao Residents-Nationality)
