<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Turkish Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Following are major news items
in leading Turkish newspapers on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Milliyet (National)
</P>
<P>
-- The U.S. warplanes Monday took off from the Incirlik Airbase
in Adana, southern Turkey, and fired at an Iraqi target in a
no-fly zone in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The U.S.-led allies set up the no-fly zone in northern Iraq
after the 1991 Gulf War allegedly to protect Kurds living in the
area.
</P>
<P>
Hurriyet (Freedom)
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Prime Minister designate Yalim Erez Monday held
talks on formation of a new government with pro-Islamic Virtue
Party (FP) leader Recai Kutan, Motherland Party (ANAP) leader
Mesut Yilmaz and Democratic Left Party (DSP) Chairman Bulent
Ecevit.
</P>
<P>
He has gained full support from the ANAP and the DSP. However,
True Path Party (DYP) leader Tansu Ciller is expected to reject
Erez's proposal for the establishment of the new government.
</P>
<P>
Sabah (Morning)
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel on Tuesday will chair a
meeting of the National Security Council at the presidential
palace to discuss the fundamentalism and terrorism in Turkey.
</P>
