<HEADLINE> Estrada Grants Financial Aid to Poor Towns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada has approved the immediate release of financial assistance
to some 300 poor municipalities, the Philippine News Agency said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Jinggoy E. Estrada, President Estrada's
son and national president of the League of Municipalities of the
Philippines (LMP), the agency said.
</P>
<P>
President Estrada initially directed the Department of Budget
and Management to release some 82 million pesos (2.05 million U.S.
dollars) to the first 12 municipalities.
</P>
<P>
Based on the LMP chief's evaluation, the initial amount will
directly benefit more than 1,500 employees and more than 120,000
constituents of the impoverished towns which could therefore pay
their local workers' salaries, incentives and bonuses and provide
the basic services to their people. 
</P>
