<HEADLINE> China Concerned About Situation in Sierra Leone: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government is
deeply concerned about the situation in Sierra Leone, according to
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao here today.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government hopes that the situation in Sierra
Leone will remain peaceful and stable," said Zhu, when asked to
comment on the current situation in the county at a news briefing
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Chinese government has all along appreciated
and supported the efforts made jointly by Sierra Leone's
popularly-elected government and the Economic Community of West
Africa States to restore peace in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the spokesman said, the efforts made by Sierra Leone
to achieve peace and stability should have the sympathy and
support of the international community, including Sierra Leone's
neighboring countries.  
