<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Attracts More Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Zambia attracted investment
licenses worth over 951 million U.S. Dollars in the first half of
this year compared to the total pledged investment of about 272
million Dollars of last year.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest monthly review of the economy,
Business Trends, published by Standard Chartered Bank, of the 951
million Dollars, 40 percent represented the mining investment, Roan
Antelope (India), and the planned rehabilitation of power
infrastructure by the Zambia Electricity Supply Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Experts observed that potential investors have put Zambia
on hold awaiting the eventual privatization of the Zambia
Consolidated Copper Mines (ZCCM), the mainstay of the country's
economy.
</P>
<P>
The bank said that without considerable research it is
impossible to tell what proportion of the investment pledges are
converted into the actual projects which could also lead to job
creation.
</P>
<P>
However, a rough rule of the thumb applied internationally is
that 50 percent of investment pledges are made into actual
projects and if such a ratio is attained in Zambia, then
investment spending will increase substantially in the early
years of the 21st century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981229.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National People's Congress Concludes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The sixth meeting of the
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee ended today
with passage of a number of legislative items, including the
Securities Law.
</P>
<P>
The Securities Law, which includes 214 articles in 12 chapters,
covers the issuance of stocks, purchases of listed companies,
securities trading, standards of conduct governing securities
companies, the securities regulatory department and industry
associations.
</P>
<P>
The law, which goes into effect on July 1, 1999, accentuates
the market principles of openness, equality and fairness. It also
prohibits cheating, insider trading and market manipulation.
</P>
<P>
The new las stipulates that the A-share market is limited to
domestic investors, with a strict prohibition against any form of
involvement on the part of foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
The Law on Military Service, which reduces the term of active
duty of 3-4 years to 2 years, will enter effect immediately
after promulgation.
</P>
<P>
The Decision Concerning the Crack Down on Crimes in Foreign
Exchange stipulates a maximum penalty of life imprisonment for
illegal activities.
</P>
<P>
Today's NPC Standing Committee meeting approved a number of
other decisions and reports, including a decision regarding the
implementation of the Law on Nationality in the Macao Special
Administrative Region after China's resumption of sovereignty over
the region in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Another decision called for the establishment of a work
committee to examine and supervise implementation of the budget.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, presided over
the meeting and outlined legislative plans for the next four
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
