<HEADLINE> China Accelerates Coal Gas Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- China plans to introduce
preferential loan and fee exemption policies to accelerate the
development of coal gas, one of the nation's main new energy
resources.
</P>
<P>
China has developed over 50 coal gas projects, including a
650,000-cu.m. gas storage tank and coal gas pipeline stretching
620,000 meters, according to a senior official with the
Administration of Coal Industry.
</P>
<P>
Current figures indicate the country's total coal gas usage
during 1998 will exceed 400 million cu.m., with the figure
representing a substantial rise for previous years.
</P>
<P>
The government has decided to promote the coal gas industry by
eliminating compensation fees for enterprises engaged in the
initial stages of exploration and development. Preferential loans
will also be available for key coal gas projects.
</P>
<P>
China has placed priority on the development of coal gas in
order to compensate for shortfalls in the energy supply, according
to the official. The increased use of coal gas is expected to
improve the country's consumption structure for energy resources,
reduce air pollution and enhance safe production.
</P>
<P>
China has abundant coal gas resources. Coal fields in north,
northeast and south China have estimated recoverable coal gas
deposits of over 3.5 billion cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the nation has developed an extensive array of
advanced coal gas technology, including some 20 technological
items which reach international standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
