<HEADLINE> Second West-East Power Line Enters Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 29 (Xinhua) -- China's second west-east
power transmission line linking Guizhou and Guangdong provinces
recently entered operations.
</P>
<P>
The line, completed at a cost of 1.83 billion yuan (220.48
million US dollars), raises the transmission capacity from the
South China inter power grid in the west to the Guangdong power
grid in the east to over 1.35 million kilowatts. Experts note that
the line has also improved connections between power grids in
Guangdong, Guangxi, Yunnan and Guizhou provinces and the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
The transmission line linking the Tianshengqiao Power Station
in Guizhou with Luodong in Guangdong was constructed in two
phases. The 316-km first phase section was completed in 1995, with
the 637-km second phase section recently entering operations.
</P>
<P>
The country's first west-east power transmission line, which
links Guizhou, Guangxi, Yunnan and Guangdong was completed in
June 1993.  
</P>
</TEXT>
