<DOCNO> XIE19981229.0185 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Settles Citizenship Question </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The National People's Congress
(NPC) Standing Committee, China's top legislative body, today
approved the Explanations on Implementation of the Law on
Nationality in the Macao Special Administrative Region
(MSAR).
</P>
<P>
China will deal with questions concerning the nationality of
Macao residents in a flexible manner which fully complies with the
basic principles of the Law on Nationality and considers
both the reality and history of the region.
</P>
<P>
The Explanations read:
</P>
<P>
-- All Macao residents of Chinese descent who were born on
Chinese territory, including Macao, and those fulfilling the
requirements of the Law on Nationality are Chinese citizens,
regardless of whether they do or do not hold Portuguese travel
certificates or identity cards.
</P>
<P>
Individuals of both Chinese and Portuguese descent are free to
choose between Chinese or Portuguese citizenship. However, prior
to exercising their citizenship option, MSAR residents enjoy all
rights set forth in the Basic Law of the Macao Special Economic
Region, with the exception of the rights restricted by the Law on
Nationality.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese residents in the MSAR holding Portuguese travel
documents can continue to use such documents to travel to other
countries and regions following the founding of the MSAR. However,
in Macao and other parts of China they do not enjoy the protection
of Portuguese consulates because they hold such documents.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese residents in the MSAR with residence rights in other
countries can travel to other countries and regions with
appropriate documents signed by foreign governments. However, in
Macao and other parts of China they do not enjoy the protection of
foreign consulates because they hold such documents.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese residents of the MSAR who return from overseas
either before or after the founding of the MSAR can apply for a
change of citizenship at related departments on the strength of
valid documents.
</P>
<P>
-- The Central Government entrusts the Government of the Macao
SAR to designate departments to handle matters related to
nationality applications in accordance with China's Law on
Nationality and the aforementioned stipulations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981229.0186 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-29 </DATE_TIME>
