<HEADLINE> China Initiates Levee Reinforcement Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, December 29 (Xinhua) -- China recently initiated a
major project to reinforce a vulnerable section of the Yangtze
River levee as part of an effort to combat possible major floods.
</P>
<P>
The project, which is expected to cost 1.95 billion yuan (234.9
million US dollars), focuses on the Jiujiang Levee. Heavy summer
flooding breached the levee and inundated some sections and
threatened the entire city of Jiujiang.
</P>
<P>
The Jiujiang project, the first Yangtze project of its kind
approved by the central government, is designed to repair and
consolidate banks, dikes and levees along a 196 km. section from
the city of Ruichang to Pengze County. Experts point to potential
problems along 75 percent of the levee in the section.
</P>
<P>
The project is scheduled for completion within three
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
