<HEADLINE> Tianjin Fulfills Annual Container Transport Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, the leading port city
in north China, handled 1.08 million ton equivalent unit (TEU)
containers during 1998 and fulfilled its annual target four days
ahead of schedule, according to a port official.
</P>
<P>
The harbor's total handling volume hit 67.48 million tons, with
the annual target of 60 million tons fulfilled 42 days ahead of
schedule.
</P>
<P>
The total volume of coke products handled in the first 11
months of the year grew by 8.5 percent on the 1997 period, with
the figure for mineral ore rising by 9.6 percent, chemical fertilizers up
by 11.63 percent, iron and steel up 57.2 percent and bulk goods up
6.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The official predicted marked growth for the handling capacity
in 1999.  
</P>
