<HEADLINE> Ermei Mountain Opens Rail System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 29 (Xinhua) -- A new rail system opened
recently on scenic Ermei Mountain in southwest China's Sichuan
Province to carry tourists to Wanfo (10,000 Buddhas) Peak, the
mountain's highest peak.
</P>
<P>
Tourists were previously limited to visits to Jin (gold) Peak
which rises 3,077 meters above the sea level. Bus routes and
pathways provided access to the peak Ermei, one China's four
major Buddhist shrines.
</P>
<P>
The single-track rail system, the highest of its kind in the
world, reaches Wanfo Peak at 3,099 meters above sea level.
</P>
<P>
The eight-minute ride along the 2,100-meter system offers
breathtaking views of verdant green forests and magnificent
snow-capped peaks. Wanfo Peak is an ideal place to view the rising
sun, peaks shrouded by clouds and the legendary "Buddhist
rays". 
</P>
</TEXT>
