<HEADLINE> New Zealand Sees Thousands of Teen Abortions in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of young New
Zealand females had an abortion last year, according to data
released by the NZ Youth Affairs Ministry Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, 2,962 abortions were carried out on females aged
between 11 and 19 years.
</P>
<P>
Also in 1997, nearly 300 under 15 year-olds contracted a
sexually transmitted decease (STD) and were treated at an STD
clinic. A further 6,843 teenagers (15-19-year-old) with STDs
sought help from clinics nationwide. Under-19-year-olds made up 21
percent of all patients attending STD clinics nationwide.
</P>
<P>
However, the ministry believes the real number of youngsters
with STDs was probably much higher.
</P>
<P>
A specialist committee under the ministry has raised
recommendations including compulsory sexual health education in
primary schools and a huge campaign using various media such as
youth television and magazines.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand Youth affairs Minister Tony Ryall called on parents
to share responsibility for their children's sexual health.
</P>
<P>
"It is not just the responsibility of the school, it is the
responsibility of families," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
