<HEADLINE> Fire Kills 7 in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, December 28 (Xinhua) -- A fire that broke out Monday in
a fireworks market in the Peruvian capital city of Lima burned
dead 7 people and injured six, leaving the shopping malls and
warehouses in the market in ruins.
</P>
<P>
The fire started when a retailer lighted a "rocket
firecracker" which shot into the sky and then found its way into
a fireworks warehouse. The people in the market rushed to get
water from the toilet in a futile attempt to put out the fire,
which triggered a chain of explosions.
</P>
<P>
The fire was extinguished two hours later after fire fighters
joined the rescue efforts. Seven bodies were found in the ashes
and all were female, including two children.
</P>
<P>
A government official who inspected the fire site said the
police seized several hundred kilograms of fireworks products in
the market not long before.
</P>
<P>
She urged people to stop selling fireworks for their potential
threats to people's lives. 
</P>
