<DOCNO> XIE19981229.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam plans to export 3.9m tons of rice in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam planned to export 3.9
million tons of rice in 1999, Vietnam's English daily "Vietnam
News" reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The plan to this effect was included in a decision signed last
week by Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Van Khai.
</P>
<P>
Under the decision, next year's rice exports will be divided
into two periods to ensure Vietnam's national food security.
</P>
<P>
In the first period, between January 1 and September 30, the
country will allow up to 3.24 million tons of rice to be
exported.
</P>
<P>
In September, a decision will be made regarding exports of the
remaining volume of 660,000 tons, depending on the actual amount
of rice harvested and the operations of rice exporters.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has harvested a record 31.8 million tons of rice this
year. The figure overshot the planned target by 800,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam exported an estimated 3.8 million tons of rice this
year, or about 400,000 tons more than the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The National Assembly of Vietnam has targeted food output of 32
million tons for next year, or 200,000 tons more than this year.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
