<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Province Defers Personnel Transfers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 29 (Xinhua) -- All transfers of public
servants in Sri Lanka's North Western Province have been put off
till January 31, 1999 in view of the forthcoming provincial
council election there, officials said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
An official of the Ministry of Public Administration said the
decision has been conveyed by the ministry to secretaries of all
ministries, divisional secretaries and heads of government
departments and institutions.
</P>
<P>
In a circular the ministry said that this decision was made at
the request of the Commissioner of Elections to postpone all
transfers effect from January 1 in the province till the end of
January.
</P>
<P>
The commissioner made this request because public officers have
to serve on election duties, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The election to the North Western Provincial Council is
scheduled for January 25, 1999, in which 446 candidates will
contest for 52 council seats including two bonus seats for the
province comprising the two districts of Kurunegala and Puttalam.
</P>
