<HEADLINE> Vietnam Steps up Fight Against Drug Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 29 (Xinhua) -- As many as 682 drug-related
cases were detected with the arrest of 1,149 people and
confiscation of 4.1 kg and 4,719 doses of heroin and 23.6 kg of
opium in the first 15 days of the two-month massive crackdown on
drug-related criminals in the country, Vietnam news agency (VNA)
has reported.
</P>
<P>
The crackdown was launched by the government from November 30
to ask policemen, customs officers and border guards to step up
the fight against drug criminals and to encourage the entire
society to take part in the fight against drug abuse.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's authorities detected 7,643 drug-related cases with
15,595 people involved in the first 11 months of this year, VNA
Monday quoted the national drug committee as saying.
</P>
<P>
In this period, 38.44 kg of heroin and 629.7 kg of opium were
confiscated, VNA said, adding courts at various levels tried 2,807
cases with 4,306 people accused, and with 35 people sentenced to
death and 19 others to prison for life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
