<HEADLINE> 55 Fires Occur in Myanmar in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 29 (Xinhua) -- A total of 55 fires broke out
in Myanmar in November, causing losses of 124,466 U.S. dollars,
the official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the fires, 46 were due to negligence, four to electrical
faults and five were arson cases.
</P>
<P>
However, the report did not mention any deaths or injuries
caused by the fires.
</P>
<P>
The authorities are urging departments concerned to take fire
prevention measures to reduce fire outbreaks. Villages are also
urged to take special prevention measures to ensure fires do not
break out at warehouses where agricultural products are kept.
</P>
<P>
In the first 10 months of this year, Myanmar recorded 115 fire
cases, most in early January, which killed 17 people and 200
animals, destroyed 178 houses, three factories, five warehouses
and left 817 people homeless. 
</P>
</TEXT>
