<HEADLINE> Cross-Straits Trade Port Enters Operations in Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINJIANG, December 29 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province
opened a new wharf for ships of 10,000 dead weight ton (dwt)
today to promote trade cross the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
The multi-purpose wharf is part of the first phase project at
Jinjiang's Weitou Port. The first phase was completed at a cost
of 140 million yuan and will have an annual handling capacity of
480,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Plans call for the construction of 22 berths for ships of
500-50,000 dwt.
</P>
<P>
Two container ships left the port today on their maiden voyage
to Hong Kong. 
