<HEADLINE> Koznick Wins World Cup Slalom Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Kristina Koznick of the United
States won her first World Cup victory of the season at
Semmering, Austria, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Koznick twisted her way around the 58 gates down the
Hirschenkogel course in a combined time of 1 minute 40.49
seconds, beating Switzerland's Karin Roten to the second place by
0.84 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Pernilla Wiberg of Sweden clocked the third fastest time,
coming home in 1:41.37, 0.51 seconds ahead of Spela Pretnar of
Slovenia.
</P>
<P>
Koznick trailed Pretnar by 0.01 seconds. But she posted a
brilliant second leg to take her second career World Cup
victory. 
</P>
