<HEADLINE> European Stock Markets Maintain High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 28 (Xinhua) - With the birth of the euro only
three days away and the absence of London markets - closed for
Bank Holiday - European stock markets Monday continued to build on
their pre-Christmas gains.
</P>
<P>
Frankfurt's blue-chip Xetra DAX index rose above the 5000
points for the first time this month despite the low trading
volume before the euro currency's January 1 launch.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said enough investors were making traditional
end-of-the-year purchases for the DAX to extend its gains.
</P>
<P>
The electronically traded Xetra DAX closed up 61.53 points, or
1.24 percent, at 5040.15 points while the floor DAX climbed 1.88
percent to 5044.77.
</P>
<P>
The CAC-40 index closed up 0.68 points to close at 3873.10
while trading volume stood at Ffr 4.5bn. "Anyone with an order can
move this market, volumes are so thin, and most people are very
disinterested," said one trader.
</P>
<P>
"We've seen very little activity today, there are very few
people around and nobody wants to make any big move," said another
Paris dealer. 
